0001.name: Bulbasaur
0001.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

Pokédex entries.entry: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

0002.name: Ivysaur
0002.description: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

Pokédex entries.entry: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

0003.name: Venusaur
0003.description: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

Pokédex entries.entry: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

0004.name: Charmander
0004.description: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

Pokédex entries.entry: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

0005.name: Charmeleon
0005.description: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

Pokédex entries.entry: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

0006.name: Charizard
0006.description: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

Pokédex entries.entry: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

0007.name: Squirtle
0007.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

Pokédex entries.entry: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

0008.name: Wartortle
0008.description: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

Pokédex entries.entry: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

0009.name: Blastoise
0009.description: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

Pokédex entries.entry: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

0010.name: Caterpie
0010.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

0011.name: Metapod
0011.description: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

Pokédex entries.entry: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

0012.name: Butterfree
0012.description: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

Pokédex entries.entry: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

0013.name: Weedle
0013.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

Pokédex entries.entry: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

0014.name: Kakuna
0014.description: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

Pokédex entries.entry: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

0015.name: Beedrill
0015.description: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

Pokédex entries.entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

0016.name: Pidgey
0016.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

Pokédex entries.entry: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

0017.name: Pidgeotto
0017.description: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

Pokédex entries.entry: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

0018.name: Pidgeot
0018.description: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

Pokédex entries.entry: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

0019.name: Rattata
0019.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

Pokédex entries.entry: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

0020.name: Raticate
0020.description: It uses its whis­ kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

Pokédex entries.entry: It uses its whis­ kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

0021.name: Spearow
0021.description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

Pokédex entries.entry: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

0022.name: Fearow
0022.description: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

Pokédex entries.entry: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

0023.name: Ekans
0023.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

Pokédex entries.entry: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

0024.name: Arbok
0024.description: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

Pokédex entries.entry: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

0025.name: Pikachu
0025.description: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

Pokédex entries.entry: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

0026.name: Raichu
0026.description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

0027.name: Sandshrew
0027.description: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

Pokédex entries.entry: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

0028.name: Sandslash
0028.description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

Pokédex entries.entry: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

0029.name: Nidoran-f
0029.description: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

Pokédex entries.entry: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

0030.name: Nidorina
0030.description: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

Pokédex entries.entry: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

0031.name: Nidoqueen
0031.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

0032.name: Nidoran-m
0032.description: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

Pokédex entries.entry: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

0033.name: Nidorino
0033.description: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

Pokédex entries.entry: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

0034.name: Nidoking
0034.description: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

Pokédex entries.entry: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

0035.name: Clefairy
0035.description: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

0036.name: Clefable
0036.description: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

Pokédex entries.entry: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

0037.name: Vulpix
0037.description: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

Pokédex entries.entry: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

0038.name: Ninetales
0038.description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

Pokédex entries.entry: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

0039.name: Jigglypuff
0039.description: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

Pokédex entries.entry: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

0040.name: Wigglytuff
0040.description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

Pokédex entries.entry: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

0041.name: Zubat
0041.description: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

Pokédex entries.entry: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

0042.name: Golbat
0042.description: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

Pokédex entries.entry: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

0043.name: Oddish
0043.description: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

Pokédex entries.entry: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

0044.name: Gloom
0044.description: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

Pokédex entries.entry: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

0045.name: Vileplume
0045.description: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

Pokédex entries.entry: It has the world’s largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

0046.name: Paras
0046.description: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by draw­ ing nutrients from the bug host.

Pokédex entries.entry: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by draw­ ing nutrients from the bug host.

0047.name: Parasect
0047.description: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

Pokédex entries.entry: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

0048.name: Venonat
0048.description: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

Pokédex entries.entry: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

0049.name: Venomoth
0049.description: The dustlike scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

Pokédex entries.entry: The dustlike scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

0050.name: Diglett
0050.description: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

Pokédex entries.entry: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

0051.name: Dugtrio
0051.description: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

Pokédex entries.entry: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

0052.name: Meowth
0052.description: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn’t get along with Galarian Meowth.

Pokédex entries.entry: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn’t get along with Galarian Meowth.

0053.name: Persian
0053.description: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

Pokédex entries.entry: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

0054.name: Psyduck
0054.description: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

Pokédex entries.entry: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

0055.name: Golduck
0055.description: Often seen swim­ ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

Pokédex entries.entry: Often seen swim­ ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

0056.name: Mankey
0056.description: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

Pokédex entries.entry: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

0057.name: Primeape
0057.description: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

Pokédex entries.entry: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

0058.name: Growlithe
0058.description: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

Pokédex entries.entry: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

0059.name: Arcanine
0059.description: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

Pokédex entries.entry: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

0060.name: Poliwag
0060.description: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

0061.name: Poliwhirl
0061.description: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

Pokédex entries.entry: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

0062.name: Poliwrath
0062.description: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

Pokédex entries.entry: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

0063.name: Abra
0063.description: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

Pokédex entries.entry: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

0064.name: Kadabra
0064.description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

Pokédex entries.entry: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

0065.name: Alakazam
0065.description: Its brain can out­ perform a super­ computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its brain can out­ perform a super­ computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

0066.name: Machop
0066.description: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

Pokédex entries.entry: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

0067.name: Machoke
0067.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

0068.name: Machamp
0068.description: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

Pokédex entries.entry: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

0069.name: Bellsprout
0069.description: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

Pokédex entries.entry: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

0070.name: Weepinbell
0070.description: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

Pokédex entries.entry: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

0071.name: Victreebel
0071.description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

Pokédex entries.entry: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

0072.name: Tentacool
0072.description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

Pokédex entries.entry: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

0073.name: Tentacruel
0073.description: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

Pokédex entries.entry: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

0074.name: Geodude
0074.description: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

Pokédex entries.entry: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

0075.name: Graveler
0075.description: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

Pokédex entries.entry: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

0076.name: Golem
0076.description: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

0077.name: Ponyta
0077.description: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

0078.name: Rapidash
0078.description: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

Pokédex entries.entry: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

0079.name: Slowpoke
0079.description: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Pokédex entries.entry: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

0080.name: Slowbro
0080.description: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

Pokédex entries.entry: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

0081.name: Magnemite
0081.description: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

Pokédex entries.entry: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

0082.name: Magneton
0082.description: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

Pokédex entries.entry: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

0083.name: Farfetchd
0083.description: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

Pokédex entries.entry: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

0084.name: Doduo
0084.description: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

Pokédex entries.entry: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

0085.name: Dodrio
0085.description: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

Pokédex entries.entry: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

0086.name: Seel
0086.description: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

Pokédex entries.entry: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

0087.name: Dewgong
0087.description: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

Pokédex entries.entry: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

0088.name: Grimer
0088.description: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

Pokédex entries.entry: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

0089.name: Muk
0089.description: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

Pokédex entries.entry: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

0090.name: Shellder
0090.description: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

0091.name: Cloyster
0091.description: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

Pokédex entries.entry: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

0092.name: Gastly
0092.description: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

Pokédex entries.entry: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

0093.name: Haunter
0093.description: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an­ other dimension.

Pokédex entries.entry: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an­ other dimension.

0094.name: Gengar
0094.description: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

Pokédex entries.entry: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

0095.name: Onix
0095.description: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

Pokédex entries.entry: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

0096.name: Drowzee
0096.description: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

Pokédex entries.entry: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

0097.name: Hypno
0097.description: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

Pokédex entries.entry: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

0098.name: Krabby
0098.description: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

0099.name: Kingler
0099.description: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

Pokédex entries.entry: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

0100.name: Voltorb
0100.description: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

Pokédex entries.entry: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

0101.name: Electrode
0101.description: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

Pokédex entries.entry: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

0102.name: Exeggcute
0102.description: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

Pokédex entries.entry: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

0103.name: Exeggutor
0103.description: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

Pokédex entries.entry: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

0104.name: Cubone
0104.description: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON's real face.

Pokédex entries.entry: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON's real face.

0105.name: Marowak
0105.description: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

Pokédex entries.entry: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

0106.name: Hitmonlee
0106.description: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

Pokédex entries.entry: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

0107.name: Hitmonchan
0107.description: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

Pokédex entries.entry: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

0108.name: Lickitung
0108.description: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

0109.name: Koffing
0109.description: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

Pokédex entries.entry: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

0110.name: Weezing
0110.description: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

Pokédex entries.entry: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

0111.name: Rhyhorn
0111.description: A POKéMON with a one-track mind. Once it charges,  it won't stop running until it falls asleep.

Pokédex entries.entry: A POKéMON with a one-track mind. Once it charges,  it won't stop running until it falls asleep.

0112.name: Rhydon
0112.description: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

Pokédex entries.entry: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

0113.name: Chansey
0113.description: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

Pokédex entries.entry: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

0114.name: Tangela
0114.description: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to sea­ weed. Its vines shake as it walks.

Pokédex entries.entry: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to sea­ weed. Its vines shake as it walks.

0115.name: Kangaskhan
0115.description: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

Pokédex entries.entry: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

0116.name: Horsea
0116.description: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

Pokédex entries.entry: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

0117.name: Seadra
0117.description: Capable of swim­ ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

Pokédex entries.entry: Capable of swim­ ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

0118.name: Goldeen
0118.description: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

0119.name: Seaking
0119.description: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

Pokédex entries.entry: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

0120.name: Staryu
0120.description: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

Pokédex entries.entry: If its body is torn, it can grow back if the red core remains. The core flashes at midnight.

0121.name: Starmie
0121.description: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

0122.name: Mr-mime
0122.description: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

Pokédex entries.entry: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

0123.name: Scyther
0123.description: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

Pokédex entries.entry: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

0124.name: Jynx
0124.description: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

Pokédex entries.entry: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

0125.name: Electabuzz
0125.description: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

Pokédex entries.entry: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

0126.name: Magmar
0126.description: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

0127.name: Pinsir
0127.description: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

Pokédex entries.entry: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

0128.name: Tauros
0128.description: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

Pokédex entries.entry: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

0129.name: Magikarp
0129.description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

Pokédex entries.entry: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

0130.name: Gyarados
0130.description: Once it begins to rampage, a GYARADOS will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

Pokédex entries.entry: Once it begins to rampage, a GYARADOS will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

0131.name: Lapras
0131.description: A POKéMON that has been over­ hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

Pokédex entries.entry: A POKéMON that has been over­ hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

0132.name: Ditto
0132.description: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

Pokédex entries.entry: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

0133.name: Eevee
0133.description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

0134.name: Vaporeon
0134.description: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

Pokédex entries.entry: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

0135.name: Jolteon
0135.description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.

Pokédex entries.entry: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.

0136.name: Flareon
0136.description: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

Pokédex entries.entry: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

0137.name: Porygon
0137.description: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

Pokédex entries.entry: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

0138.name: Omanyte
0138.description: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

Pokédex entries.entry: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

0139.name: Omastar
0139.description: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

Pokédex entries.entry: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

0140.name: Kabuto
0140.description: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

Pokédex entries.entry: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

0141.name: Kabutops
0141.description: Its sleek shape is perfect for swim­ ming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

Pokédex entries.entry: Its sleek shape is perfect for swim­ ming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

0142.name: Aerodactyl
0142.description: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

Pokédex entries.entry: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

0143.name: Snorlax
0143.description: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

Pokédex entries.entry: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

0144.name: Articuno
0144.description: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

Pokédex entries.entry: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

0145.name: Zapdos
0145.description: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

Pokédex entries.entry: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

0146.name: Moltres
0146.description: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

Pokédex entries.entry: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

0147.name: Dratini
0147.description: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

Pokédex entries.entry: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

0148.name: Dragonair
0148.description: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

Pokédex entries.entry: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

0149.name: Dragonite
0149.description: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

Pokédex entries.entry: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

0150.name: Mewtwo
0150.description: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

Pokédex entries.entry: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

0151.name: Mew
0151.description: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.

Pokédex entries.entry: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
